wwpLeosNtpClientMIB.name: wwpLeosNtpClientMIB

revisions.description: Added the wwpLeosNtpClientSyncChangeNotifAdminState. Changed wwpLeosNtpClientSyncState to read-only.
Add new MIB OIDs to support IP protocol version independent Inet addressing. New attributes include: wwpLeosNtpServerResolvedInetAddr, wwpLeosNtpServerResolvedInetAddrType.

Added new objects wwpLeosNtpClientDrift, wwpLeosNtpClientFastOffset, wwpLeosNtpClientSlowOffset, wwpLeosNtpClientNtpOffset, wwpLeosNtpServerState wwpLeosNtpClientNtpFastStartMode and deprecated wwpLeosNtpClientOffset.
Added client offset, delay and jitter attributes
Added the wwpLeosNtpAuthTable and other objects used for MD5 authentication
Deprecated the wwpLeosNtpServerUserPri and the wwpLeosNtpServerDhcpPri objects.

wwpLeosNtpClientMIB.contactinfo: Mib Meister 115 North Sullivan Road Spokane Valley, WA 99037 USA Phone: +1 509 242 9000 Email: support@ciena.com
wwpLeosNtpClientMIB.description: This MIB module defines the managed objects for the NTP client on LEOS based WWP devices.

Md5Key.name: Md5Key
Md5Key.description: Represents the textual convention which defines the name string and display hint

wwpLeosNtpClientState.name: wwpLeosNtpClientState
wwpLeosNtpClientState.description: Setting this object to 'enable' will enable the NTP client on Ciena devices.

wwpLeosNtpClientMode.name: wwpLeosNtpClientMode
wwpLeosNtpClientMode.description: Setting this object to 'broadcast' will cause the client not to poll the NTP server at all. Instead, it will wait for configured NTP servers to broadcast their current time. When the client receives the first message, it will retrieve a reliable time from that server. If it is set to polling then device will poll the NTP server.

wwpLeosNtpClientPollFreq.name: wwpLeosNtpClientPollFreq
wwpLeosNtpClientPollFreq.description: The polling frequency at which NTP server will be polled if the NTP client is configured to be in polling mode. The value of this object should be multiple of 16. The change in the NTP mode will only be effective when NTP client is enabled and should not be set at the same time either Min or Max polling frequency is set.

wwpLeosNtpClientTable.name: wwpLeosNtpClientTable
wwpLeosNtpClientTable.description: Table of NTP server information indexed by wwpLeosNtpServerIndex. To create an entry in the table, use SNMP multiple set operation and following objects must be set: wwpLeosNtpServerAddr and wwpLeosNtpServerStatus. To use MD5 authentication, wwpLeosNtpServerKeyId must be set at the time of creation along with wwpLeosNtpServerAddr and wwpLeosNtpServerStatus, otherwise no MD5 authentication will be used.

wwpLeosNtpClientEntry.name: wwpLeosNtpClientEntry
wwpLeosNtpClientEntry.description: An entry for each NTP server.

wwpLeosNtpServerIndex.name: wwpLeosNtpServerIndex
wwpLeosNtpServerIndex.description: Specifies the unique index of the entry.

wwpLeosNtpServerAddrType.name: wwpLeosNtpServerAddrType
wwpLeosNtpServerAddrType.description: Specifies the type of address wwpLeosNtpServerAddr belongs to.

wwpLeosNtpServerAddr.name: wwpLeosNtpServerAddr
wwpLeosNtpServerAddr.description: The IP address or host name of the NTP server.

wwpLeosNtpServerResolvedAddr.name: wwpLeosNtpServerResolvedAddr
wwpLeosNtpServerResolvedAddr.description: Specifies the resolved IP address if wwpLeosNtpServerAddr is set to host name. If wwpLeosNtpServerAddr is set to IP address then wwpLeosNtpServerResolvedAddr will be the same as wwpLeosNtpServerAddr. If the IP address is an IPv6, this OID will be set to 0.0.0.0 and the wwpLeosNtpServerAddrType will be set to other(0).

wwpLeosNtpServerUserPri.name: wwpLeosNtpServerUserPri
wwpLeosNtpServerUserPri.description: This object is no longer implemented as the NTP client determines the server's relative priority or preference relative to other configured servers. Reads will always return 1 and writes will be quietly ignored. This object was once used to specify the user priority of the wwpLeosNtpServerAddr.

wwpLeosNtpServerDhcpPri.name: wwpLeosNtpServerDhcpPri
wwpLeosNtpServerDhcpPri.description: This object is no longer implemented as the NTP client determines the server's relative priority or preference relative to other configured servers. Reads will always return 1 and writes will quietly be ignored. This object was once used to specify the dhcp priority of the wwpLeosNtpServerAddr.

wwpLeosNtpServerUserAdminState.name: wwpLeosNtpServerUserAdminState
wwpLeosNtpServerUserAdminState.description: This object is used to specify the user admin state of the wwpLeosNtpServerAddr.

wwpLeosNtpServerScope.name: wwpLeosNtpServerScope
wwpLeosNtpServerScope.description: This object is used to specify the scope for the entry. It specifies if the entry is configured by dhcp/user/both.

wwpLeosNtpServerOperState.name: wwpLeosNtpServerOperState
wwpLeosNtpServerOperState.description: This object is used to specify the operational state of the wwpLeosNtpServerAddr.

wwpLeosNtpServerStatus.name: wwpLeosNtpServerStatus
wwpLeosNtpServerStatus.description: To create a row in this table, a manager must set this object to 'createAndGo'. The server added will only be effective when NTP client is enabled. To create entry in the table use SNMP multiple set operation and following objects must be set wwpLeosNtpServerAddr and wwpLeosNtpServerStatus.

wwpLeosNtpServerKeyId.name: wwpLeosNtpServerKeyId
wwpLeosNtpServerKeyId.description: This object is used to specify the MD5 key ID that that the server will use. A 0 key ID implies no MD5 key.

wwpLeosNtpServerState.name: wwpLeosNtpServerState
wwpLeosNtpServerState.description: This object reflects the current connection status of the server.

wwpLeosNtpServerResolvedInetAddrType.name: wwpLeosNtpServerResolvedInetAddrType
wwpLeosNtpServerResolvedInetAddrType.description: Specifies the type of address wwpLeosNtpServerResolvedInetAddr belongs to. When set to: ipv4 : wwpLeosNtpServerResolvedInetAddr should be compliant with InetAddressIPv4 from RFC 4001 ipv6 : wwpLeosNtpServerResolvedInetAddr should be compliant with InetAddressIPv6 from RFC 4001.

wwpLeosNtpServerResolvedInetAddr.name: wwpLeosNtpServerResolvedInetAddr
wwpLeosNtpServerResolvedInetAddr.description: Specifies the resolved IP address if wwpLeosNtpServerAddr is set to host name. If wwpLeosNtpServerAddr is set to IP address then wwpLeosNtpServerResInetAddr will be the same as wwpLeosNtpServerAddr. The InetAddress specified here will be compliant with RFC 4001.

wwpLeosNtpAuthTable.name: wwpLeosNtpAuthTable
wwpLeosNtpAuthTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the key-id and MD5 key.

wwpLeosNtpAuthEntry.name: wwpLeosNtpAuthEntry
wwpLeosNtpAuthEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the wwpLeosNtpAuthTable.

wwpLeosNtpAuthKeyId.name: wwpLeosNtpAuthKeyId
wwpLeosNtpAuthKeyId.description: This object specifies the key ID. It is also used as index in the table.

wwpLeosNtpAuthMd5Key.name: wwpLeosNtpAuthMd5Key
wwpLeosNtpAuthMd5Key.description: Used to specify the MD5 key to use with this key identifier.

wwpLeosNtpAuthRowStatus.name: wwpLeosNtpAuthRowStatus
wwpLeosNtpAuthRowStatus.description: To create a row in this table, a manager must set this object to 'createAndGo'. The server added will only be effective when NTP client is enabled. To create entry in the table use SNMP multiple set operation and following objects must be set: wwpLeosNtpAuthKeyId and either wwpLeosNtpAuthMd5Key or wwpLeosNtpAuthMD5KeyEnc.

wwpLeosNtpAuthMD5KeyEnc.name: wwpLeosNtpAuthMD5KeyEnc
wwpLeosNtpAuthMD5KeyEnc.description: Used to specify the encrypted MD5 key to use with this key identifier.

wwpLeosNtpClientMD5State.name: wwpLeosNtpClientMD5State
wwpLeosNtpClientMD5State.description: Set to true to use MD5 authentication for NTP

wwpLeosNtpClientDrift.name: wwpLeosNtpClientDrift
wwpLeosNtpClientDrift.description: The Drift in micro-seconds of the local clock. This value is only valid when NTP is enabled and has a valid peer.

wwpLeosNtpClientFastOffset.name: wwpLeosNtpClientFastOffset
wwpLeosNtpClientFastOffset.description: The Fastest Offset seen in micro-seconds of the local clock. This value is only valid when NTP is enabled and has a valid peer.

wwpLeosNtpClientSlowOffset.name: wwpLeosNtpClientSlowOffset
wwpLeosNtpClientSlowOffset.description: The Slowest Offset seen in micro-seconds of the local clock. This value is only valid when NTP is enabled and has a valid peer.

wwpLeosNtpClientMinPollFreq.name: wwpLeosNtpClientMinPollFreq
wwpLeosNtpClientMinPollFreq.description: The polling freq at which NTP server will be polled if the NTP client is configured to be in polling mode and is not currently synchronized to an NTP server. The value of this object should be multiple of 16. The change in the ntp mode will only be affective when ntp client is enabled and should not be set at the same time PollFreq is set.

wwpLeosNtpClientMaxPollFreq.name: wwpLeosNtpClientMaxPollFreq
wwpLeosNtpClientMaxPollFreq.description: The polling freq at which NTP server will be polled if the NTP client is configured to be in polling mode and is currently synchronized to an NTP server. The value of this object should be multiple of 16. The change in the ntp mode will only be affective when ntp client is enabled and should not be set at the same time PollFreq is set.

wwpLeosNtpClientOffset.name: wwpLeosNtpClientOffset
wwpLeosNtpClientOffset.description: When NTP is synchronized, this contains the difference between the reference clock and the system clock micro-seconds.

wwpLeosNtpClientDelay.name: wwpLeosNtpClientDelay
wwpLeosNtpClientDelay.description: When NTP is synchronized, this indicates the round trip time in micro-seconds taken by the reply packet to return in response, to a query sent by the server.

wwpLeosNtpClientJitter.name: wwpLeosNtpClientJitter
wwpLeosNtpClientJitter.description: When NTP is synchronized, it indicates the magnitude of jitter between several time queries in micro-seconds.

wwpLeosNtpClientNtpOffset.name: wwpLeosNtpClientNtpOffset
wwpLeosNtpClientNtpOffset.description: When NTP is synchronized, this contains the difference between the reference clock and the system clock micro-seconds.

wwpLeosNtpClientNtpFastStartMode.name: wwpLeosNtpClientNtpFastStartMode
wwpLeosNtpClientNtpFastStartMode.description: Setting this object to 'on' will cause the NTP client to set it's time to the first reply received from a synchronized NTP server, the first time this occurs after the NTP client is enabled. After that, the normal rules for selecting and synchronizing to a server are used.

wwpLeosNtpMulticastTable.name: wwpLeosNtpMulticastTable
wwpLeosNtpMulticastTable.description: Table of NTP Multicast Addresses indexed by wwpLeosNtpMulticastIndex. To create an entry in the table, use SNMP multiple set operation and following objects must be set: wwpLeosNtpMulticastInetAddrType and wwpLeosNtpMulticastInetAddr.

wwpLeosNtpMulticastEntry.name: wwpLeosNtpMulticastEntry
wwpLeosNtpMulticastEntry.description: An entry for each NTP multicast addresses.

wwpLeosNtpMulticastIndex.name: wwpLeosNtpMulticastIndex
wwpLeosNtpMulticastIndex.description: Specifies the unique index of the entry.

wwpLeosNtpMulticastInetAddrType.name: wwpLeosNtpMulticastInetAddrType
wwpLeosNtpMulticastInetAddrType.description: Specifies the type of address wwpLeosNtpMulticastInetAddr belongs to. When set to: ipv4 : wwpLeosNtpMulticastInetAddr should be compliant with InetAddressIPv4 from RFC 4001 ipv6 : wwpLeosNtpMulticastInetAddr should be compliant with InetAddressIPv6 from RFC 4001.

wwpLeosNtpMulticastInetAddr.name: wwpLeosNtpMulticastInetAddr
wwpLeosNtpMulticastInetAddr.description: Specifies the NTP multicast address. The InetAddress specified here will be compliant with RFC 4001.

wwpLeosNtpMulticastRowStatus.name: wwpLeosNtpMulticastRowStatus
wwpLeosNtpMulticastRowStatus.description: To create a row in this table, a manager must set this object to 'createAndGo'. To create entry in the table use SNMP multiple set operation and following objects must be set: wwpLeosNtpMulticastInetAddrType, wwpLeosNtpMulticastInetAddr and wwpLeosNtpMulticastRowStatus.

wwpLeosNtpClientSyncChangeNotifAdminStat.name: wwpLeosNtpClientSyncChangeNotifAdminState
wwpLeosNtpClientSyncChangeNotifAdminStat.description: Set to on to turn on sync change notifications.

wwpLeosNtpClientSyncState.name: wwpLeosNtpClientSyncState
wwpLeosNtpClientSyncState.description: This object indicates the synchronized state of the NTP client.

wwpLeosNtpClientSyncStatusChangeNotifica.name: wwpLeosNtpClientSyncStatusChangeNotification
wwpLeosNtpClientSyncStatusChangeNotifica.description: This notification is sent whenever there is a change in the synchronization state for the NTP client. wwpLeosNtpClientSyncChangeNotifAdminState should be enabled to receive this trap.
